The paper discusses security engineering in the software lifecycle, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the similarity between security engineering and software engineering, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the software engineering (cs.SE) subfield. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for protecting information and systems, which could fall under the subfields of cryptography (cs.CY) and security and privacy (cs.SI). Finally, the paper outlines a systematic mapping process, which could be relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) subfield.
